get.description: Interface-specific parameters for the IPv4 address family.

forwarding.description:
Indicates whether IPv4 packet forwarding is enabled or
          disabled on this interface.

mtu.description:
The size, in octets, of the largest IPv4 packet that the
          interface will send and receive.

ip.description: The IPv4 address of the neighbor node.

prefix-length.description: The length of the subnet prefix.

netmask.description: The subnet specified as a netmask.

origin.description: The origin of this neighbor entry.

link-layer-address.description: The link-layer address of the neighbor node.

get.description:
Parameters to control the autoconfiguration of IPv6
          addresses, as described in RFC 4862.

create-global-addresses.description:
If enabled, the host creates global addresses as
            described in RFC 4862.

create-temporary-addresses.description:
If enabled, the host creates temporary addresses as
            described in RFC 4941.

temporary-valid-lifetime.description:
The time period during which the temporary address
            is valid.

temporary-preferred-lifetime.description:
The time period during which the temporary address is
            preferred.
